div.div:
Refactor encoding handling and improve logging functionality
- Updated project configuration to include new library dependencies: libiconv_1_17d.lib and LightLogWriteImplLibd.lib. - Changed encoding identifiers in encodings.inc from "char" and "wchar_t" to "CHAR_T" and "WCHAR_T" for clarity. - Added new binary files for LightLogWriteImplLib and libiconv_1_17, including their respective PDB and IDB files. - Enhanced the main.cpp file with additional encoding detection and conversion functions, including BOM handling for UTF-8, UTF-16LE, and UTF-16BE. - Updated test functions to include new encoding conversion tests and improved logging for better traceability. - Cleaned up the logging output in test_log.log to reflect successful conversions and removed redundant error messages. - Added new output files for various encoding conversions to the testdata/output directory, ensuring comprehensive testing coverage.

Refactor and enhance encoding conversion utility
- Removed obsolete test files and scripts related to UTF-8 generation. - Updated `generate_test_files.py` to include new encoding formats and BOM options. - Added `LightLogWriteImpl` header file for a lightweight logging library with thread-safe implementations. - Introduced new log files and updated logging mechanisms to capture conversion errors. - Implemented batch file conversion functionality in `main.cpp` with detailed logging. - Added new test data files for GB2312 and updated existing test files for consistency. - Removed unnecessary local encoding test files and adjusted output files for clarity.
